2026-02-03 | Check if an Array is Trionic

	Question
Given an integer array nums,  
return true if nums is trionic, otherwise return false.

	Approach
1.	Start from index 0 and move forward while the sequence is strictly increasing.
2.	Mark the index **p** where the increasing sequence ends.
	-	If no increase happens or we reach the end, return false.
3.	From index p, move forward while the sequence is strictly decreasing.
4.	Mark the index **q** where the decreasing sequence ends.
	-	If no decrease happens or we reach the end, return false.
5.	From index q, move forward while the sequence is strictly increasing.
6.	If this final increasing sequence reaches the last index (n âˆ’ 1),
	-	and all three phases were valid,
	-	then the array is trionic.
7.	Otherwise, return false.
8.	Time Complexity: O(n)  
   Space Complexity: O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    bool isTrionic(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        if (n < 4) return false;

        int i = 0;

        // 1. Strictly increasing
        while (i + 1 < n && nums[i] < nums[i + 1]) {
            i++;
        }
        if (i == 0 || i == n - 1) return false;
        int p = i;

        // 2. Strictly decreasing
        while (i + 1 < n && nums[i] > nums[i + 1]) {
            i++;
        }
        if (i == p || i == n - 1) return false;
        int q = i;

        // 3. Strictly increasing
        while (i + 1 < n && nums[i] < nums[i + 1]) {
            i++;
        }

        return i == n - 1;
    }
};
